IsDynamic.description: Whether the send port is dynamic or static

IsTwoWay.description: Determines whether the port is two-way

SecondaryTransport.description: Secondary transport of the static send port.

SendPipeline.description: Send pipeline used to send data sent through this port.

SendPipelineData.description: Custom configuration specific to this instance of the usage of the pipeline.

ReceivePipeline.description: Receive pipeline used to receive a response when a message is sent out through this port.

ReceivePipelineData.description: Custom configuration information specific to the current instance of the receive pipeline.

InboundTransforms.description: Collection of inbound transforms of two-way send port

OutboundTransforms.description: Collection of outbound transforms of send port

Tracking.description: Desired level of document tracking for the send port.

EncryptionCert.description: Encryption certificate that is used to encrypt data sent through this port.

Filter.description: Optional filter expression used for this send port.

RouteFailedMessage.description: Gets or sets a value indicating whether or not failed messages are routed to failed message subscribers.

OrderedDelivery.description: Floag specifying whether or not the send port orders the delivery of messages.

StopSendingOnFailure.description: Flag indicating whether or not the send port stops sending messages on a failure.

OrderedDelivery.description: Flag that specifies whether the BizTalk Message Queuing adapter supports ordered delivery.

ServiceWindowEnabled.description: Flag that specifies whether the service window is enabled.

FromTime.description: Start time for the service window.

ToTime.description: End time for the service window.
